Get the request_token

Run req_access_token.py
Open the printed kite.login_url() in your browser
Log in on Kite
Copy the request_token from the redirect URL



Generate the access_token

Put that request_token into access_token.py:
Run access_token.py
It will print:
Your access_token: <ACCESS_TOKEN>

Update the bot config

Your bot uses MIS_Trailing_SL_bot.py and loads:
KITE_API_KEY
KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN
Put those into your .env file, or export them before running:

KITE_API_KEY=abcdefghi
KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN=<ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_SCRIPT>


Run the bot

After updating KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN, start MIS_Trailing_SL_bot.py
The bot calls:

self.kite.set_access_token(self.access_token)

